-- Bug #673: `check` false-greened (exit 0) on a multi-module program that
-- `run`/`build` reject, DROPPING a cross-module constrained-function's call
-- obligation on the LOCATED (check) path.  `println : Display a => a -> …` is
-- imported from the prelude (core); a value from imported `array.get` feeds a
-- 6-tuple, and Display impls exist only to arity 5.  The Display obligation was
-- recorded from the PER-MODULE schemeObligationsRef, which has no entry for a
-- cross-module binding, so instantiateVarTracked silently took the plain
-- `instantiate` path and dropped it — check reported nothing while run/build
-- (whose dict elaboration is a separate net) rejected.  DISTINCT from #40's
-- string-interp `display`-method path (an IMPL obligation, already checked):
-- this is the imported-FUNCTION call obligation.  Fix: fall back to the
-- persistent cross-module qual tables (bareCrossModuleObls) when the per-module
-- table misses.  MUST stay multi-module (an import triggers the module path).
import array.{get}

main =
  let v = match get 0 [|1|]
    Some x => x
    None => -1
  println (v, v, v, v, v, v)
